The numbered patch stack in patches/ is applied to the PPSSPP source tree by
build.sh and modifies PPSSPP's own files. It adds the debugger and headless
behavior documented in README.md, including savestates, screenshots, execution
control, isolated GUI sessions, and request-correlated asynchronous replies. It
is therefore a derivative work of PPSSPP (GPL-2.0-or-later) and is licensed
GPL-2.0-or-later. emucap does not ship PPSSPP's binary or source — build.sh
clones and builds a pinned upstream commit on your machine. See ../../NOTICE.

